reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars I Will Be Returning This Product
reviews.reviewText: Despite the appearance of the product on its Amazon page (the box image presented does not match the actual product sent), this is NOT a Canon Ink Cartridge Set.It is apparently made by a competitor to Canon. I learned (the hard way) years ago the many printer manufacturers install firmware on their machines that cause "disruption of function" if they detect the installation of non-brand name ink cartridges.Since I don't want my printer to become an expensive non-functioning "paperweight", I will have to return this product to the shipper.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I own a Canon Pixma MG7520 printer that I bought in 2014. For the past for the past 2 years, I've been using this ink. It's 1/3 the cost of the Canon brand ink and there's no difference in quality that I can detect. Also, unlike "ink refills" I've tried in the past, these cartridges are recognized by the printer and you'll see the "low ink" (or "out of ink") message when using the printer. I'm definitely a satisfied customer!

reviews.reviewTitle: Seems to be just as good a genuine OEM
reviews.reviewText: Item just as described and works perfectly. Full set of ink barely more than one small one at store. Plus it gets delivered right to your door.
